@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Pacifico');

table.wiki-content-table {
    width: 100%;
}

.center-header {
    font-size: 150%;
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 1em;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted currentColor;
    padding-bottom: 0.25em;
}

.item-table {
    font-size: 1em;
    width: 90%;
    text-align: center;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.250em auto;
}

.table-header td {
    font-size: 1.1em;
    font-weight: 900;
    background: #b9c9fe;
    border-top: 0.250rem solid #aabcfe;
    border-bottom: 0.0625rem solid #fff;
    color: #039;
    text-align: center;
}

.item-table td {
    background: #e8edff;
    border-bottom: 0.125rem solid #fff;
    border-right: 0.0625rem solid #fff;
    border-top: 0.125rem solid transparent;
    border-left: 0.0625rem solid transparent;
    color: #669;
    padding: 0.5em;
}

.item-table  ul {
    padding-inline-start: 1.5em;
}

.item-table td:nth-of-type(1), 
.item-table td:nth-of-type(2) {
    text-align: center;
}

div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(2) > tbody > tr > td:nth-child(1) {
    width: 60%;
}

div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(2) > tbody > tr > td:nth-child(2) {
    text-align: left;
}

#page-content > .collapsible-block {
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.75em;
    background-color: lightgrey;
    border-top: 0.125rem dashed slategrey;
    border-bottom: 0.125rem dashed slategrey;
}

#page-content > .collapsible-block .collapsible-block-content {
    text-align: left;
}

div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content th {
    text-align: center;
}

#page-content > div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(3) > tbody > tr:nth-child(3) > td:nth-child(2) {
    color: darkred;
    background-color: rgba(193,31,32,0.25);
    text-align: center;
    width: 25%;
}

#page-content > div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(1) > tbody > tr:nth-child(3) > td:nth-child(2),
#page-content > div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(2) > tbody > tr:nth-child(3) > td:nth-child(2),
#page-content > div:nth-child(19) > div.collapsible-block-unfolded > div.collapsible-block-content > table:nth-child(4) > tbody > tr:nth-child(3) > td:nth-child(2) {
    color: darkgreen;
    background-color: rgba(90,137,32,0.25);
    text-align: center;
    width: 25%;
}
[[/module]]


Welcome to my author page! I'm [[*user Devonmartin]]. I'm a teacher who likes to write in his spare time. So let's get right to it!

Articles marked with a ⭐ have been featured on the [https://scp.cafe/ SCP Café podcast].
Articles marked with a ⚖️ are collaborative (co-authored) works.

[[span class="center-header"]]SCP Mainlist Articles[[/span]]

[[collapsible show="▼ SCP-4134: Claymore Anti-Personnel Mimes ▼" hide="▲ SCP-4134: Claymore Anti-Personnel Mimes ▲"]]

[[module ListPages name="SCP-4134"]]
|| **Item # (Rating):** %%title_linked%% (+%%rating%%) || **Title:** Claymore Anti-Personnel Mimes ||
|| **Object Class:** --Keter-- --Neutralized-- Euclid  || **Date:** 11 April 2019 ||
||||= **Details** ||
||||< A memetic pattern of behavior affecting Parisian mimes whenever the city is threatened. Three iterations of SCP-4134 documentation are currently available at your security clearance level. ||
||||= **Author's Notes** ||
|||| My first SCP! I learned more about mimes and the French Resistance for this piece than I care to admit, especially considering I scrapped 99% of it in revisions. ||
[[/module]]
[[/collapsible]]

[[collapsible show="▼ ⭐ SCP-4152: BASEMENT LOVE, Acrylic on canvas ▼" hide="▲ ⭐ SCP-4152: BASEMENT LOVE, Acrylic on canvas ▲"]]

[[module ListPages name="SCP-4152"]]
|| **Item # (Rating):** %%title_linked%% (+%%rating%%)  || **Title:** BASEMENT LOVE, Acrylic on canvas ||
|| **Object Class:** Safe  || **Date:** 9 May 2019 ||
||||= **Details** ||
||||< A painting which implants traumatic childhood memories into those with none of their own. Or does it cause one to recall suppressed memories of trauma that actually happened? ||
||||= **Author's Notes** ||
|||| My sibling and I are very tight. This article is based not only on the painting they created (see inside), but also on the experiences we shared growing up with a narcissistic parent. ||
||||= **[https://scp.cafe/2019/05/18/recap-2019-week-20/ Featured on the SCP Cafe podcast!]** (9:38) ||
[[/module]]
[[/collapsible]]

[[collapsible show="▼ ⭐ SCP-4297: The Emu-lution of War ▼" hide="▲ ⭐ SCP-4297: The Emu-lution of War ▲"]]

[[module ListPages name="SCP-4297" tags="-joke"]]
|| **Item # (Rating):** %%title_linked%% (+%%rating%%)  || **Title:** The Emu-lution of War ||
|| **Object Class:** Keter  || **Date:** 30 May 2019 ||
||||= **Details** ||
||||< In the real world, in 1932, the Australian army failed in an attempt to exterminate a group of emus. In the SCP universe, the emus fought back. ||
||||= **Author's Notes** ||
|||| Australian wildlife does //not// mess around. I had a lot of trouble coming up with an ending to the piece, and as a result I'm not completely satisfied with the pacing in the middle. I might come back and rewrite the ending someday, who knows. ||
||||= **[https://scp.cafe/2019/06/07/recap-2019-week-23/ Featured on the SCP Cafe podcast!]** (4:02) ||
[[/module]]
[[/collapsible]]


[[collapsible show="▼ ⚖️ SCP-4714: Dr. Wondertainment's My Unicorn Friend™ ▼" hide="▲ ⚖️ SCP-4714: Dr. Wondertainment's My Unicorn Friend™ ▲"]]

[[module ListPages name="SCP-4714" tags="-joke"]]
|| **Item # (Rating):** %%title_linked%% (+%%rating%%)  || **Title:** Dr. Wondertainment's [[span style="font-family: Pacifico;"]]My Unicorn Friend[[/span]]™ ||
|| **Object Class:** Safe  || **Date:** 30 June 2019 ||
||||= **Details** ||
||||< Read [[[isabels-happy-meal|this Tale]]] first for a better reading experience. Featuring Dr. Isabel Wondertainment, V and Chaz Ambrose (of Ambrose Restaurants fame)!||
||||= **Author's Notes** ||
|||| This piece was co-authored with [[*user Crashington]] as part of [[[collaboration-contest|Collab-Con 2019]]]. ||
[[/module]]
[[/collapsible]]
---------

[[span class="center-header"]]Joke Articles[[/span]]

[[collapsible show="▼ SCP-4297-J: Normal Australian Wildlife ▼" hide="▲ SCP-4297-J: Normal Australian Wildlife ▲"]]
[[module ListPages name="SCP-4297-J" tags="joke"]]
|| **Item # (Rating):** %%title_linked%% (+%%rating%%) || **Title:** Normal Australian Wildlife ||
|| **Object Class:** Apollyon  || **Date:** 31 May 2019 ||
||||= **Details** ||
||||< "Roughly 40% of SCP-4297-J eggs hatch into additional SCP-4297-J instances. The remaining 60% are delicious." ||
||||= **Author's Notes** ||
|||| YET ANOTHER EMU WAR SCIP. When I originally started brainstorming about the Emu War, I couldn't decide whether to do a -J or a mainlist scip. SO I WENT WITH BOTH! True story, this took about two hours from start to finish. According to the SCP Cafe podcast, this may be the first time an author has ever published a -J concurrently with a new mainlist article... cool! ||
[[/module]]
[[/collapsible]]





